  "text": "Finally, the in vitro respiratory activity of soils (soil C mineralization potential) was determined by estimating the CO 2 released from soil samples moistened to 60% of their water holding capacity at 24±1ºC, measured periodically for a period of 40 days with a Carmhograph-12 (Wösthoff) gas analyser [CITATION_1] ; the results referred to total mineralisation coefficient, taking into account that each soil had a different organic matter content, and was defined as milligrams of carbon released per 100 g of soil carbon per day. ",
